					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A collection of works by Ḥayim Vital.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="v">
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḳovets mi-kitve yad rabi Ḥayim Vital </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">קבץ מכתבי רח"ו</title>
							<note>
								<p>On this manuscript see <ref target="Avivi_2008" type="page">301-303</ref>, vol. 1; <ref target="Ale_sefer" type="number">11</ref> (1983), p. 104.</p>
								<p>Folios 5r-55v - Derush Adam ḳadmon (folios 5r-38r in the handwriting of Ezra of Fano).  </p>
								<p>Folios 56r-77v - Sodot. </p>
								<p>Folios 78r- 87v - Kaṿanot ha-tefilah ṿe-minhage ha-Ar"i (in the handwriting of Ezra of Fano, with additions from the manuscripts of Menahem Azariah of Fano and Nathan Ottolenghi). </p>
								<p>Folios 88r-109r - Derushim ṿe-kaṿanot nosafim le-rabi Ḥayim Vital. </p>
								<p>Folios 110r-121v - Liḳute be-ḳabalah me-et ḥakhme Tsefat (e.g., Abraham Galante, Moses Cordovero, Joseph Ashkenazi, etc.). </p>
							</note>
							<locus from="1r" to="121v"/>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">Vital, Ḥayyim ben Joseph, 1542-1620 </persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">ויטל, חיים בן יוסף, 1542-1620</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>121 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>200</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>170</height>
										<width>95</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>121 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
									<p>Original Hebrew foliation.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Leaves on guards.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained.</p>
									<p>Much water-damaged with occasional loss of text.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="29 38" writtenLines="29 38">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Additions and comments in the margin.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian cursive scripts of the 16th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Ezra of Fano</name>: folios 5r-38r.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>An entry of sale between the inheritants of <name type="person" role="owner">Eliyah of Fano</name> and <name type="person" role="owner">Shelomoh of Parmigiani (?)</name>: folio 5r.</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Dominico Irosolomitano</name>, Italian censor (active 1575-1624): inscribed with his name (folio 121v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">61</ref>, and appendix § 62-74.
</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Giovanni Domenico Carretto</name>, Italian censor (active 1600-1624): inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1623</date> (folio 38r, 55v, 87v, 109r, 121r); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">100-101</ref>, and appendix § 80-84.</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Alessandro Scipione</name>, Italian censor (fl. 1575-1599): inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1597</date> (folio 121v). </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Derush Adam Kadhma'ah. Etc. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional MS. 27,186.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
